2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute mi_ha from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • some hedimX == 3 into 1
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

To compute mi_ha_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if mi_ha == 1, mi_ha_age = heagb
  • if mi_ha == 0, mi_ha_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, mi_ha_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w1 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w1$id)
ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w1$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha[which(ELSA_w1$hedim01 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedim02 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedim03 == 
    3 | ELSA_w1$hedim04 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedim05 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedim06 == 3 | 
    ELSA_w1$hedim07 == 3)] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha[which(ELSA_w1$hedim01 == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha[which(ELSA_w1$hedim01 == -8)] <- 998

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w1$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha_age[which(ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha_age[which(ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha == 1)] <- car::recode(ELSA_w1$heagb[which(ELSA_ds_w1$mi_ha == 
    1)], "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997")

2.1.2.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute mi_ha from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • some hedimX == 3 into 1
  • hedia01 == -9 and hedimX == -1 into 997
  • hedia01 == -8 and hedimX == -1 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

To compute mi_ha_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if mi_ha == 1, mi_ha_age = HeAgbRY - ybirth
  • if mi_ha == 0, mi_ha_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, mi_ha_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w2$id)
ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha[which(ELSA_w2$hedim01 == 3 | ELSA_w2$hedim02 == 3 | ELSA_w2$hedim03 == 
    3 | ELSA_w2$hedim04 == 3 | ELSA_w2$hedim05 == 3 | ELSA_w2$hedim06 == 3 | 
    ELSA_w2$hedim07 == 3 | ELSA_w2$hedim08 == 3)] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha[which(ELSA_w2$hedia01 == -9 & ELSA_w2$hedim01 == -1)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha[which(ELSA_w2$hedia01 == -8 & ELSA_w2$hedim01 == -1)] <- 998

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha == 1 & !ELSA_w2$HeAgbRY %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9))] <- ELSA_w2$HeAgbRY[which(ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha == 1 & !ELSA_w2$HeAgbRY %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9))] - ELSA_w2$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha == 1 & !ELSA_w2$HeAgbRY %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9))]
ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w2$mi_ha_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;NA=999")

2.1.3.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute mi_ha from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • dhedimmi == 1 into 1
  • dhedimmi == 0 into 0
  • dhedimmi == -1 into 996

To compute mi_ha_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if mi_ha == 1, mi_ha_age = heagbry - ybirth
  • if mi_ha == 0, mi_ha_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, mi_ha_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w3 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w3$id)
ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha <- car::recode(ELSA_w3$dhedimmi, "-1=996")

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w3$id))
ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha == 1 & !ELSA_w3$heagbry %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9) & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)] <- ELSA_w3$heagbry[which(ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha == 
    1 & !ELSA_w3$heagbry %in% c(-1, -8, -9) & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)] - ELSA_w3$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha == 
    1 & !ELSA_w3$heagbry %in% c(-1, -8, -9) & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)]
ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w3$mi_ha_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;NA=999")

2.1.4.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute mi_ha from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • hedimmi == 1 into 1
  • hedimmi == -9 into 997
  • hedimmi == -8 into 998
  • hedimmi == 0 into 0

To compute mi_ha_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if mi_ha == 1, mi_ha_age = heagbry-ybirth
  • if mi_ha == 0, mi_ha_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -2 into 991
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, mi_ha_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w4$id)
ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha <- car::recode(ELSA_w4$hedimmi, "-8=998;-9=997")

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w4$id))
ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha == 1 & !ELSA_w4$heagbry %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9, -2))] <- ELSA_w4$heagbry[which(ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha == 1 & !ELSA_w4$heagbry %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9, -2))] - ELSA_w4$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha == 1 & !ELSA_w4$heagbry %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9, -2))]
ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w4$mi_ha_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;-2=991;NA=999")
